## 9. Trigger Disable/Enable for Data Repairs

When immutability triggers are in place and a data repair is needed:

```sql
-- 1. Disable the specific trigger
ALTER TABLE {table} DISABLE TRIGGER {trigger_name};

-- 2. Perform the repair (targeted, with RETURNING to confirm)
UPDATE {table} SET ... WHERE id = '{specific_id}' RETURNING id, {changed_columns};

-- 3. Re-enable immediately
ALTER TABLE {table} ENABLE TRIGGER {trigger_name};

-- 4. Verify trigger is active
UPDATE {table} SET notes = 'test' WHERE id = '{specific_id}';
-- Should fail with immutability error
```

Never leave a trigger disabled. Always verify re-enablement in the same SQL session.

